criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Cardiac surgeries with extracorporeal circulation in patients older than 18 years

          -  Written and signed informed consent

          -  Preanesthetic assessment and preoperatory exams in accordance with study methodology

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Active infection;

          -  Previously coagulopathy;

          -  Antiplatelet therapy use until 10 days before surgery (except acetylsalicylic acid and
             enoxaparin that may be used in prophylactic doses until 24h before surgery);
